  "prompt": "Does Moto G4 support Reliance Jio 4G?",
  "response": "Yes, the **Moto G4** (and its variants like the Moto G4 Plus) supports **Reliance Jio 4G**. The device is compatible with Jio's 4G LTE network, which operates on the **Band 3 (1800 MHz)** and **Band 5 (850 MHz)** frequencies in India. \n\nHere\u2019s how to confirm compatibility:\n\n1. **4G Bands**: Moto G4 supports LTE Band 3 and Band 5, which are used by Jio.\n2. **VoLTE Support**: The Moto G4 also supports **VoLTE (Voice over LTE)**, which is required to make voice calls on Jio\u2019s 4G-only network.\n\nTo use Reliance Jio on your Moto G4:\n- Insert the Jio SIM card.\n- Ensure that VoLTE is enabled in the device settings (usually found under **Mobile Network** settings).\n\nIf VoLTE is not enabled by default, you may need to enable it manually or update the device software.",
